Queen D has done it again! 

For her 4th time, Delaney has qualified for the World Championship Team after winning two national titles in the Women’s 10m and Women’s 10m Synchro events at the USA Diving Senior National Championships this past week. 

The World Championship will be held in Fukuoka, Japan from July 14-22.

Bronze medalist and an Olympic quota spot for Team USA 🇺🇸🥉 

For those that don’t know, I hit my feet on the second round dive causing us to score only 38 points on the dive. From there on out we had to claw our way back into the event. We knew it was gonna be a fight but we didn’t give up hope! This one brought me to tears not because of the medal, but because I was so proud of myself and Jessica for fighting back despite things going wrong. We believed in ourselves and in one another to get the job done! Knowing we could come back from that shows how much we are capable of! THAT is what makes this bronze medal so much more special!

Thank you to @jessicaparratto for trusting in me and providing  words of encouragement to “keep fighting” during that event. I would not have wanted to share this moment with anyone else. 

Thank you @arizonadive_ddumais for encouraging me to fight. And apologies for giving you a few grey hairs last night. 😬

And thank you to @drew_johansen for continuing to believe in me as Jess’s synchro partner! We are one heck of a team!

Qualified for the finals and earned Team USA an Olympic quota spot! Today was my first individual event on the international stage since the Olympics and overall I’m happy and proud of myself for how I handled the day. But I know I have so much more left in the tank! Ready to have fun and enjoy the moment in the finals tomorrow night! Tune in live on peacock at 5 AM EST on July 19th!
27 meters high… I think I’ll stick to 10 meters 😳 #cliffdiving #highdiving

Fourth World Championships ✅

While I am walking away with a bronze medal, a 6th place finish in individual, and 2 Olympic quota spots, I do not feel satisfied. I know my diving was not where it needs to be. But I wouldn’t change a thing, because the lessons I’m walking away with are far more valuable than a shiny award. The lessons learned this past month may just be what I need to set me up for this upcoming Olympic year! I’m more ready than ever to get back to work, but first a much needed break. #neversatisfied #alwayshungry

@laney_schnell of @arizonaswimdive has earned national and international competition medals, but the lessons learned in the journey are what she treasures most. Today, the 2023 NCAA Woman of the Year Top 30 honoree continues to evolve into her best self. 🌟

#NCAAWOTY | Link in bio

Wow! Top 30 at the NCAA Woman of the Year event! It was a huge honor to stand next to the other 29 amazing women with such incredible stories to tell. I could not be more humbled and in awe of each one of them. 

Thank you @azathletics and @ncaa for providing me with experiences and memories I will cherish for the rest of my life! And huge thank you to my people who came to celebrate with me last night! I cannot be more appreciative of each one of you! ❤️
